        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 22 at 3:55PM EDT by NWS Wakefield VA</headline>
        <description>At 354 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Littleton, or 13 miles northeast of Warrenton, moving northeast at 25
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Gasburg around 400 PM EDT.
Barley around 415 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Ante, Brink, Pleasant
Hill, Gum Forks, Triplet, Roanoke Rapids Lake, Henrico, Turners
Crossroads, Vultare, and Valentines.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
